	     Durban – A man’s body was found floating at the Kloof Country Club, west of Durban on Thursday, police said. The Durban search and rescue unit recovered the body of the unknown man who had drowned allegedly while picking up golf balls at the club, said Captain Nqobile Gwala. “The cause of drowning is unknown at this stage,” Gwala said.  Gwala said Pinetown police are investigating an inquest docket and circumstances around the incident.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  